      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "aRect",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A rectangle that defines a region of the view for tracking mouse-entered and mouse-exited events."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "userObject",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The object that gets sent the event messages. It can be the view itself or some other object (such as an NSCursor or a custom drawing tool object), as long as it responds to both "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsresponder/1529306-mouseentered"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsresponder/1527561-mouseexited"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "userData",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Data stored in the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsevent"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " object for each tracking event."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "flag",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "If "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", the first event will be generated when the cursor leaves "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "aRect"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", regardless if the cursor is inside "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "aRect"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " when the tracking rectangle is added. If "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/no"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " the first event will be generated when the cursor leaves "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "aRect"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " if the cursor is initially inside "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "aRect"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", or when the cursor enters "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "aRect"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " if the cursor is initially outside "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "aRect"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ".  You usually want to set this flag to "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/no"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A tag that identifies the tracking rectangle. It is stored in the associated "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsevent"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects and can be used to remove the tracking rectangle."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Tracking rectangles provide a general mechanism that can be used to trigger actions based on the cursor location (for example, a status bar or hint field that provides information on the item the cursor lies over). To simply change the cursor over a particular area, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsview/1483540-addcursorrect"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". If you must use tracking rectangles to change the cursor, the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nscursor"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class specification describes the additional methods that must be invoked to change cursors by using tracking rectangles."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In macOS 10.5 and later, tracking areas provide a greater range of functionality (see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsview/1483489-addtrackingarea"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ")."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
